==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foretoken
<hw>Fore"to`ken</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>foret⟦amac⟧cen</ets>. See <er>Token</er>.]</ety> <def>Prognostic;
previous omen.</def> <rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foretoken</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Foretoken
<hw>Fore*to"ken</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Foretokened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Foretokening</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>foret⟦amac⟧cnian</ets>; <ets>fore + t⟦amac⟧cnian</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To foreshow; to presignify; to prognosticate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whilst strange prodigious signs <qex>foretoken</qex> blood.</q>
<rj><qau>Daniel.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Foretold</ent>⟦br⟧
